A **loan moratorium** (EMI holiday) lets you pause EMI payments for 3–12 months. While it provides short-term cash-flow relief, the unpaid interest is added to your principal, increasing the total loan cost and often extending the tenure. This calculator shows the exact extra interest cost and tenure extension from a moratorium on any loan.
